    "long_instructions": "### Sound Design Challenge\r\nYou're now a sound designer, and your challenge is to create an immersive soundscape that tells a story using everything you've learned about filters, delays, volume, sequencing, layering, and offsetting sounds.\r\n\r\nIf you want to pick a new song, you can click the restart button in the upper-right corner [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=start-over-button)\r\n\r\n**The Scenario:**\r\nImagine you’re designing the soundtrack for a scene in a movie. Choose one of these themes:\r\n- Mysterious Forest – A foggy landscape where distant echoes and shifting volumes create an eerie atmosphere.\r\n- Cyber City at Night – A pulsing beat, layered synths, and dynamic filters give this city its futuristic energy.\r\n- Ocean Adventure – Sailing boats, open water, and a mix of rising and falling volumes create the feeling of drifting at sea.\r\n\r\n**Do This**\r\n-Sequence your sounds: Arrange different sounds in an order that makes sense for your theme.\r\n- Layer and Offset: Try using rests, delays, and overlapping sounds to make your mix feel more natural.\r\n- Use Effects: Apply filters, delays, and volume changes to add depth to your soundscape.\r\n- Match Sound Lengths: Make sure your layers work together by adjusting lengths so they blend smoothly.\r\n\r\n**Bonus Challenge:** Try making a transition effect, like a build-up before a drop or a gradual shift from calm to intense!",
    "display_name": "Soundscape Story",
    "bubble_choice_description": "You're now a sound designer, and your challenge is to create an immersive soundscape that tells a story",
